(Overview) Tj
T*
(Listening develops attention, interpretation, and response to spoken language.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Explain the meaning of Listening in English using accurate subject vocabulary.) Tj
T*
(- Describe the key ideas behind main points, details, tone, and speaker intention.) Tj
T*
(- Apply Listening to examples such as extracting key points from an oral presentation.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid common errors and build confidence through listening for gist and details.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Detailed Explanation) Tj
T*
(What This Topic Means) Tj
T*
(Listening develops attention, interpretation, and response to spoken language. In) Tj
T*
(English, students do better when they understand not only the definition of Listening,) Tj
T*
(but also the language, symbols, and patterns that appear whenever this topic is tested.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Core Explanation) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Listening is main points, details, tone, and speaker intention. A) Tj
T*
(strong explanation should show the idea clearly, connect it to prior knowledge, and then) Tj
T*
(walk through the method students are expected to use whenever they meet this topic in) Tj
T*
(classwork or examination questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Understanding) Tj
T*
(A good classroom illustration for Listening is extracting key points from an oral) Tj
T*
(presentation. When students can talk through that kind of example slowly and correctly,) Tj
T*
(they usually find it much easier to transfer the same reasoning to new questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why Students Find It Difficult) Tj
T*
(One frequent problem in Listening is hearing words without organizing the ideas.) Tj
T*
(Students also struggle when they try to memorize final answers without understanding the) Tj
T*
(steps that make the answer valid. Clear explanations, careful checking, and repeated) Tj
T*
(guided practice reduce this difficulty.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
(In real study situations, students master Listening by practising with tasks that mirror) Tj
T*
(listening for gist and details. The topic becomes more meaningful when it is linked to) Tj
T*
(examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that reflect how English is) Tj
T*
ET
