(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on extracting key points from an oral presentation.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in main points, details, tone, and speaker intention that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Listening step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on listening for gist and details.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid hearing words without organizing the ideas while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Listening: main points, details, tone, and speaker) Tj
T*
(intention.) Tj
T*
(- Hearing words without organizing the ideas.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Listening without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Listening in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around listening for gist and details before trying harder) Tj
T*
(tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as hearing words without organizing the ideas and write) Tj
T*
(the correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Listening regularly so the method behind main points, details, tone, and) Tj
T*
(speaker intention becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Listening and describe how it fits into English.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on extracting key points from an oral presentation and) Tj
T*
(explain each step.) Tj
T*
(- Describe why hearing words without organizing the ideas causes errors and how to avoid) Tj
T*
(it.) Tj
T*
(- Answer an exam-style question that focuses on listening for gist and details.) Tj
T*
